The paper introduces a new machine learning model, the Multigranular Tsetlin Machine (MTM), which is designed for pattern recognition tasks. The paper discusses the performance of the MTM on both synthetic and real-world datasets, indicating that it is likely to be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of the MTM for image recognition tasks, suggesting that it may be relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the hyperparameter search space of the MTM, indicating that it may be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
